{%- comment -%}
  snippets/quick-view-recommendation.liquid
  =========================================
  Row 3 — full-width "You may also like" carousel inside the Quick View modal.

  Strategy:
    • Liquid renders cards at page load (section-render API call).
      Because quick-view.liquid is fetched via /products/<handle>?sections=quick-view,
      the Shopify section-render context IS a product page, so product.collections
      and product.tags are available for recommendation filtering.
    • Up to `rec_limit` sibling products from the first non-catch-all collection
      are rendered into <li> elements via {% capture %}. The current product is
      excluded so it never appears in its own recommendations.
    • After the modal body is stamped, quick-view.js fires no extra event here —
      instead this snippet emits `productcard:injected` via an inline <script>
      so product-card.js can sync wishlist + compare states immediately.
    • No JS carousel library is used; horizontal scroll is CSS-only for speed.

  Parameters:
    product    {Object}  required — current product (used to find collection &
                                    exclude the product from its own results)
    rec_limit  {Number}  optional — max cards to show (default 6)
    heading    {String}  optional — section heading (default "You may also like")
    see_all_url {String} optional — URL for "See all" link (falls back to first
                                    collection URL if found, otherwise omitted)

  JS hooks:
    [data-qv-rec]           — root wrapper; used by the inline init script below
                              as a sentinel to avoid double-init on re-render.
    [data-qv-rec-list]      — the <ul>; could be targeted for async injection.

  CSS dependency: Section 6 of assets/quick-view.css (added alongside this file).

  IMPORTANT: product-card.js must be loaded globally (it is, via theme.liquid).
    All ATC, Wishlist, Compare, and Quick View interactions inside these cards
    are handled by product-card.js event delegation on document.body — no extra
    wiring is needed here.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  assign rec_limit   = rec_limit | default: 6
  assign heading     = heading   | default: 'You may also like'

  comment
    ── Find a source collection ──────────────────────────────────────────────
    Walk the product's collections to find one that is NOT a catch-all
    ("all", "frontpage"). Prefer the first match.
  endcomment
  assign source_collection = nil
  for c in product.collections
    unless c.handle == 'all' or c.handle == 'frontpage'
      assign source_collection = c
      break
    endunless
  endfor

  comment
    ── Build the recommendation list ─────────────────────────────────────────
    Only proceed when we have a source collection with more than one product.
    We need at least 2 products so we have something to show after excluding
    the current one.
  endcomment
  assign has_recs = false
  if source_collection != nil and source_collection.products_count > 1
    assign has_recs = true
  endif

  comment
    ── "See all" URL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Caller can override via see_all_url param; otherwise fall back to the
    source collection URL so the link is always relevant.
  endcomment
  assign see_all_href = see_all_url | default: nil
  if see_all_href == nil and source_collection != nil
    assign see_all_href = source_collection.url
  endif
-%}

{%- if has_recs -%}

{%- comment -%}── Build <li> items via capture to keep logic out of markup ──{%- endcomment -%}
{%- capture rec_items_html -%}
  {%- assign shown_count = 0 -%}
  {%- for rec_product in source_collection.products -%}
    {%- if shown_count >= rec_limit -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
    {%- comment -%}Skip the product currently open in the modal{%- endcomment -%}
    {%- if rec_product.id == product.id -%}{%- continue -%}{%- endif -%}
    <li class="quick-view-rec__item">
      {%- render 'product-card',
        product:        rec_product,
        show_quickview: true,
        show_compare:   true,
        show_eta:       false
      -%}
    </li>
    {%- assign shown_count = shown_count | plus: 1 -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endcapture -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Guard: only render the section when at least one card was produced.
  (Edge case: the loop above may skip every product if the collection only
  contained the current product despite products_count > 1.)
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- unless rec_items_html == blank -%}

<div class="quick-view-rec" data-qv-rec>

  {%- comment -%}── Section header ──{%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="quick-view-rec__header">
    <h3 class="quick-view-rec__heading">{{ heading }}</h3>
    {%- if see_all_href != blank -%}
      <a
        href="{{ see_all_href }}"
        class="quick-view-rec__see-all"
        aria-label="See all products in {{ source_collection.title | escape }}"
      >
        See all
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"
             stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M3 7h8M7.5 3.5 11 7l-3.5 3.5"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
    {%- endif -%}
  </div>

  {%- comment -%}── Horizontal scroll list ──{%- endcomment -%}
  <ul class="quick-view-rec__list" data-qv-rec-list role="list">
    {{ rec_items_html }}
  </ul>

</div>

{%- comment -%}
  ── Sync wishlist + compare states ──────────────────────────────────────────
  product-card.js listens for 'productcard:injected' on document and runs
  syncWishlistButtons() + syncCompareCheckboxes() + renderCompareBar().
  We fire it inline, deferred one microtask so the DOM is committed first.
  The sentinel check on [data-qv-rec-init] prevents double-fire if the
  section is somehow re-rendered inside the same page context.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
  (function () {
    var root = document.querySelector('[data-qv-rec]:not([data-qv-rec-init])');
    if (!root) return;
    root.setAttribute('data-qv-rec-init', '1');
    Promise.resolve().then(function () {
      document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('productcard:injected', { bubbles: true }));
    });
  }());
</script>

{%- endunless -%}
{%- endif -%}
